#: ../../../admin-guide/braille-console.rst:2
msgid "Linux Braille Console"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/braille-console.rst:4
msgid ""
"To get early boot messages on a braille device (before userspace screen "
"readers can start), you first need to compile the support for the usual "
"serial console (see :ref:`Documentation/admin-guide/serial-console.rst "
"<serial_console>`), and for braille device (in :menuselection:`Device "
"Drivers --> Accessibility support --> Console on braille device`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/braille-console.rst:10
msgid ""
"Then you need to specify a ``console=brl``, option on the kernel command "
"line, the format is::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/braille-console.rst:15
msgid ""
"where ``serial_options...`` are the same as described in :ref:`Documentation/"
"admin-guide/serial-console.rst <serial_console>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/braille-console.rst:18
msgid ""
"So for instance you can use ``console=brl,ttyS0`` if the braille device is "
"connected to the first serial port, and ``console=brl,ttyS0,115200`` to "
"override the baud rate to 115200, etc."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/braille-console.rst:21
msgid ""
"By default, the braille device will just show the last kernel message "
"(console mode).  To review previous messages, press the Insert key to switch "
"to the VT review mode.  In review mode, the arrow keys permit to browse in "
"the VT content, `PAGE-UP`/`PAGE-DOWN` keys go at the top/bottom of the "
"screen, and the `HOME` key goes back to the cursor, hence providing very "
"basic screen reviewing facility."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/braille-console.rst:28
msgid ""
"Sound feedback can be obtained by adding the ``braille_console.sound=1`` "
"kernel parameter."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/braille-console.rst:31
msgid ""
"For simplicity, only one braille console can be enabled, other uses of "
"``console=brl,...`` will be discarded.  Also note that it does not interfere "
"with the console selection mechanism described in :ref:`Documentation/admin-"
"guide/serial-console.rst <serial_console>`."
msgstr ""

